Update `tokio/Cargo.toml` metadata and add a top-of-file doc note in
`tokio/src/lib.rs` so that `crates.io` and `docs.rs` both clearly
present the published artifact as `pausable-tokio` rather than as
plain tokio.

This is a publish-time-only patch. It depends on patches 0001..0004
already being applied (it does not touch any source code those
patches would conflict with).

Cargo.toml metadata changes:

  * `repository`    -> https://github.com/RookAndPawn/pausable-tokio
  * `homepage`      -> https://github.com/RookAndPawn/pausable-tokio
  * `documentation` -> https://docs.rs/pausable-tokio (added; not in upstream)
  * `description`   -> short pausable-tokio summary
  * `categories`    -> add "simulation" to the existing list
  * `keywords`      -> left as-is (upstream's "io"/"async"/"non-blocking"/
                       "futures" are still accurate)

`lib.rs` change: prepend a short `//!` doc block at the top of the
crate-level docs that explains this crate is `pausable-tokio`, points
at the runtime methods that differ, and shows the `Cargo.toml` snippet
for the typical "rename to tokio" usage. The original upstream tokio
docs follow after a horizontal rule.
diff --git a/tokio/Cargo.toml b/tokio/Cargo.toml
index b0bedbed..3f748fd1 100644
--- a/tokio/Cargo.toml
+++ b/tokio/Cargo.toml
@@ -12,13 +12,15 @@ rust-version = "1.71"
 authors = ["Tokio Contributors <team@tokio.rs>"]
 license = "MIT"
 readme = "README.md"
-repository = "https://github.com/tokio-rs/tokio"
-homepage = "https://tokio.rs"
+repository = "https://github.com/RookAndPawn/pausable-tokio"
+homepage = "https://github.com/RookAndPawn/pausable-tokio"
+documentation = "https://docs.rs/pausable-tokio"
 description = """
-An event-driven, non-blocking I/O platform for writing asynchronous I/O
-backed applications.
+A fork of tokio that adds a runtime-controllable pause/resume primitive
+on its clock. Drop-in replacement for tokio with a few extra methods on
+the Builder and Runtime types.
 """
-categories = ["asynchronous", "network-programming"]
+categories = ["asynchronous", "network-programming", "simulation"]
 keywords = ["io", "async", "non-blocking", "futures"]
 
 [features]
diff --git a/tokio/src/lib.rs b/tokio/src/lib.rs
